{{Infobox comedian|name=Teacher Mpamire|image=|imagesize=|caption=|pseudonym=|birth_name=Herbert Ssegujja|birth_date={{birth date and age|1983|9|27}}|birth_place=Mukono, Uganda|origin=|death_date=|death_place=|active=|genre=|subject=|spouse=|relatives=|signature=|website=|footnotes=}} '''Herbert Mendo Ssegujja''' (born 27 September 1983 in [[Mukono Town|Mukono]], [[Uganda]]<ref name=intw>{{Cite web|url=http://chimpreports.com/entertainment/interview-comedian-mendo-and-how-he-juggles-mimicking-museveni-and-being-teacher-mpamire/|title=Interview: Comedian Mendo and How He Juggles Mimicking Museveni and Being Teacher Mpamire|website=chimpreports.com|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref>), better known by his stage name '''Teacher Mpamire''' is a Ugandan comedian, actor and high school teacher. He is most famous for mimicking the Ugandan president, [[Yoweri Museveni|Yoweri Kaguta Museveni]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.monitor.co.ug/artsculture/Reviews/In-teacher-Mpamire-s-class--there-is-no-time-to-doze/691232-2481870-14ocr7w/index.html|title=In teacher Mpamire's class, there is no time to doze|newspaper=Daily Monitor|language=en-UK|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref>
His performances have seen him stage shows in [[Zambia]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chano8.com/teacher-mpamire-host-zambias-first-ever-comedy-class/|title=Teacher Mpamire To Host Zambia's First Ever Comedy Class|website=chano8.com|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref> [[Malawi]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://mwnation.com/kansiime-coming-back-with-teacher-mpamire-2/|title=Kansiime coming back, with Teacher Mpamire |date=2016-09-26|newspaper=The Nation Online|access-date=2017-01-10}}</ref> and other African countries.
In 2016, Teacher Mpamire was named "discovery of year" at the [[Africa Youth Awards]] held in Accra, Ghana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://matookerepublic.com/2017/01/02/comedian-teacher-mpamire-wins-africa-youth-award-to-be-honoured-by-presidents-at-au-summit/|title=Comedian Teacher Mpamire wins Africa youth award, to be honoured by presidents at AU summit|last=Abeka|first=Moses|date=2017-01-02|website=Matooke Republic|access-date=2017-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://chimpreports.com/entertainment/teacher-mpamire-voted-discovery-of-the-year-in-africa-youth-awards/|title=Teacher Mpamire Voted ‘Discovery of the Year’ in Africa Youth Awards|website=chimpreports.com|language=en-US|access-date=2017-02-07}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://bigeye.ug/teacher-mpamire-wins-continental-award/|title=Teacher Mpamire wins continental award|date=2017-01-02|newspaper=Bigeye.ug|access-date=2017-02-07|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Early life and education == Ssegujja was born in Mukono, Uganda on 27 September 1983, started his education at Bbowa primary school from where he graduated to Bbowa secondary school. He later went to Greenlight high school in Namasuba, Zana.<ref name=intw/>
At [[Kyambogo University]], Ssegujja studied for bachelor of arts in education. He eventually went to [[Makerere University]] where he studied drama.
Having been sponsored by [[Yoweri Museveni|Yoweri Kaguta Museveni]], he was admitted to the [[American Comedy Institute]] where he studied comedy performance and writing.<ref name=intw/>
